DefaultDialogue: You must be wary in these parts, traveler. The nearby farm has fallen to the Lost.  If you value your soul, I would suggest staying safely behind the walls in town.

Greetings traveler, you have the air of one new to Aeternum, so I pray the fires of hope still burn within your heart. \n\nI have taken on a daunting quest to bring aid to the needy… but I am the one now in need of assistance.

I strongly recommend that you visit the Covenant Enclave yourself. There is something inspiring about the place. \n\nIn fact, if you don't mind, it would help me greatly if you could take a message to my brother there, Lethold.

I'll return once I have tended to the needs of those stranded here in Oxboro. \n\nI do hope we can meet later, in southeastern Everfall at the enclave. My brother is there, and I think you two would get along.
At long last I return from Oxboro. I faltered at Olcott farm.  You have my eternal thanks for being there to back me up.
The whole enclave is talking about what you've been doing around here! I can't believe we met on the side of a road. \n\nI believe it's time you officially became one of us. What do you say?
We are stronger with you by our side. Holding this terrace, none of those Lost could get past us!  Aeternum is brighter with you out there, helping the humblest souls.

I've heard stories, from the battle against Corruption. It's too horrible to believe. \n\nI once thought that I could save everyone. But that's not the point, is it? It's about helping who we can. That's all we can do.
If you need shelter, the Covenant Enclave is open to you, as long as you observe our rules.  Any news from Oxboro? I am awaiting the return of an Initiate named Florina.

If you have come with hopeful dreams of enlisting with the Covenant yourself, it's only fair you know what you're getting into. \n\nA wraith stalks the lands, and some Initiates gave into fear and are now in even greater peril.

Lumen Morellus would speak with you. She can seem strange, but she is one of the most respected members of the order. \n\nShe was my mentor, and I suggest you give great consideration to her words, for she is inspired.
I have faced down all manner of darkness in my service to the Covenant.  But when such darkness comes from within our ranks, it wounds me more than any blade ever could.

Together, we have seen justice done, terror and despair purged from within our own ranks. \n\nI do hope you will consider committing your skills and courage to the Covenant. You belong with us, friend.
We must remain vigilant, always.  You and I both know only too well, evil can emerge anywhere, even from within our own ranks.
I have learned much from you in your time here. \n\nTo protect others, we must do so much more than simply keeping them from harm. Thank you, for leading by example.

You are welcome in the Covenant Hall, visitor. We keep our gates open at all hours to ensure those in despair or doubt can find the santuary they need. \n\nRemember, it only takes a spark of hope to ignite the flames of inspiration.

Be assured, you are under no pressure to join the Covenant, but you have provided us with a strong case concerning your worthiness. \n\nI must ask, however, if you can help me with another matter, one requiring some discretion.
You have recovered the relic from Invectus?  Go now, don't say a word. Simply cast it into the pyre.
You have proven yourself to be faithful and courageous, an inspiration for any whose souls are in peril. \n\nI hope you will consider joining our order, swearing your allegiance to the Covenant.

We must understand the nature of this Corruption and its dark purpose. \n\nThe shadow clouding these lands feels… strangely orchestrated. Focus, follow the threads, trust your heart and your Covenant brethren.
If it comes to it, I will stand stalwartly by you and hold this keep until they’ve ground the last brick to dust. \n\nIn this era of unprecedented darkness, you are a beacon of hope and inspiration.
Decades, nearly a century we worked this land, only to have it fall to the Lost. \n\nMy family took refuge in town, but we have nothing beyond the clothes we wore when we fled.
If you hope to convince me to leave empty-handed, you're wasting your breath.  Recover at least some of our family's things… then I will go with you.
Well now, I was having doubts, but here you are, just as you promised. This… means a lot. \n\nCovenant Initiate Florina returned to Oxboro… discouraged. Perhaps you should speak with her.
Hey! Aren't you a little young to be in here?  Don't get touchy, just a wee bit of Aeternum humor for ya!  And fear not mate, I'm as discreet as a privy guard!

Slide on over, friend! You look like one of them Marauder types. Like adventure? Maybe a bit of a scrap, aye? How about weapons and riches? \n\nHow’d you like a little tip from ol’ Tibbs? I’ve got something perfect for a new arrival.

Oh-ho, that looks like a bag of ears to me! You can… leave that there. Now show us the ring… Well done! \n\nYou’ve got a strong stomach and bravado! I got an eye for it, I do. Climb the steps, and talk to Gladiator Strou'dahia.

Oh-ho, that looks like a bag of ears to me! You can… leave that there. Now show us the ring… Well done! \n\nYou’ve got a strong stomach and bravado! I got an eye for it, I do. Climb the steps, and talk to Gladiator Strou'dahia.
We got ourselves a little quid pro quo with Everfall, keeping the Lost out of the hills and off their doorstep. \n\nEarns a drink or two. Next one is on Tibbs' tab, eh? Good luck out there!

Look, I like you mate! And I know what Strou'dahia has cooking for the new recruits. \n\nAnd if you’re keen, you could start off with a bang! Short trip, little warmup, eh? Better loot than Lugdunum to boot.

You've made it this far mate, and I can tell you'll fit right in. \n\nStrou'dahia wants to test your mettle if you're gonna join us. Swing some steel, blow those bombs, it'll be over in a flash. Recruitment procedures you see.
We got ourselves a little quid pro quo with Everfall, keeping the Lost out of the hills and off their doorstep. \n\nEarns a drink or two. Next one is on Tibbs' tab, eh? Good luck out there!
Well done! Well done indeed! No doubt the fancy folk down in Everfall are all abuzz about that last escapade, my friend. \n\nReckon I'll be telling that story for an… Aeternity. Eh? Eh?
Did I not say it from the start? I knew you would like it here, mate.  And always getting stronger, aint'cha? I look forward to the mayhem we'll bring.

Quite the journey since you first got here. Never could have seen how far you would go. And you, you were mad at me over a few ears! \n\nAnd look at us now! Always got your back, friend, through thick and thin.
Walk the grounds and watch. Warriors must train every day, especially on Aeternum.  If you want to keep up, you will have to prove yourself and challenge your limits.

Tibbs spoke of you. He's odd, but fearless. He has a unique notion of what constitutes honor, but he's a sharp fighter, keeps his enemies off-guard. \n\nIndividual freedom is as important to a Marauder as honor and glory.

When the Varangians first snuck up the cliffs and took Stonekeep, I thought them worthy opponents. Now they attack those weaker than them and forfeit any honor. \n\nWhat about you? Would you bleed for the Marauders' cause?
You have proven yourself a valiant warrior, and have friends here for what you have done. \n\nEternity is a long time. Consider spending it with us. There will never be a dull moment.
The Syndicate. The Covenant. Neither suit a combatant of your temperament.  Join our ranks and become a warrior of legend in these eternal lands.
The challenges you face in these lands will mold you. Forge yourself intently, young one. \n\nStand strong alongside your friends. Make your enemies fear your might.

You have shaped yourself into a mighty warrior. \n\nNever forget, we are both the iron and the blacksmith, and the act of forging ourselves is never ending. Hold firm in your mind what you must become.
UNUSED
Mind your step. There are some unnatural beasts in the area.  You should return to the safety of the walls. Everfall has been more dangerous as of late.
Please, please, come! You look well-equipped, and the Syndicate could pay you for your time. \n\nI see that you are new to the island? Aid me, and perhaps I can shine some light on the darkness.

Thank you for helping to resolve those, ah, unexpected consequences. We do important work here, studying Azoth's applications. But it is not without risks. \n\nPlease, come in. If you would, introduce yourself to Cleo.

Azoth… the mysterious element that runs deep in this land. It is like nothing I ever experienced in the old world. Its potential applications are vast. \n\nOur very enclave itself is built near something quite special.
Cleo has already requested a word, if you came back in one piece. I see within you the same potential.  Please, go and speak with her.
We return to the tree often.   Thank you for not disturbing the Angry Earth. Our trips are easier when they are less agitated.
Poor, poor Cleo always has something new on her mind. Discovery has hidden costs, and hers weigh heavily on her heart. \n\nThank you for helping her. She could use a friend.
Let us uncover wonderful new mysteries together.  I am happy to call you a colleague, and hopefully, in time, a good friend.
This sanctum might not be here, if not for your efforts across Aeternum. \n\nIt may be hard to see at times, but even the tiniest actions help in the face of untold suffering. Thank you, friend!
Please, if you wouldn't mind standing aside. I have many problems to unravel.  The Scriveners are always thrilled to challenge hopeful initiates, if you are looking for work.

Acquaintance of Aventus? His enthusiasm for research is admirable, but it creates complications from time to time. \n\nHe must make friends regularly. The Syndicate values those who help him uncomplicate his results.
The impermanence of death presents a peculiar conundrum when dealing with our adversaries. \n\nLet me ask you, how do you kill that which has no life? Well, we of the Syndicate aim to solve that.

I will return in time, to observe the effects of the sleeping draught and take samples. \n\nThank you for trusting in my experiment and aiding me. Maybe one day, we can save the Lost instead of pacifying them.

The Syndicate is an eclectic group, one that would be honored to have you listed amongst our ranks. \n\nPlease, if you wish to join us in the pursuit of unraveling the mysteries of Aeternum, the time is now.
You are a curious sort, perhaps the precise catalyst the Syndicate needs. \n\nOne day, you will have to tell me what transpired on that beach. I've heard rumors, but nothing beats an eyewitness.
You have proven yourself an exemplary agent of the Syndicate, time and time again. \n\nIf you had been with me in the ruins of Brimstone… things might have been different.
UNUSED
Stay resolute.
No. . . something isn't right. . .  Why can't I remember what his face looked like?
Don't get too close there, friend.  The paint isn't quite dry yet, and I'd hate to stain my hands with your blood.
Hm? A potential Initiate? If you value strength, listen well.  Do not strike out at whatever suits you in the moment. True power comes from giving that strength a purpose.
How goes the hunt? What wickedness have you put to rest?
Feel free to grab some soup, hon.  It gets mighty chilly up here and you'll need something to keep warm.
Good to see you again, hon.  I mainly keep this kitchen running for outsiders, but you can still help yourself any time.
You have my deepest appreciation for saving me from that foul crypt. \n\nThe more we learn about Corruption, the more I understand the things I saw in that cave. What I could have become…
I knew someone like you could not resist our noble cause.  The land of Aeternum will be made brighter by your strength. Stay resolute!
Welcome to the Covenant Enclave. It's a pleasure, but you haven't arrived at the best time... \n\nIf you are inclined to join the Covenant, you will need to prove yourself worthy first.

Based on what I've heard from Adjudicator Lethold and Lumen Morellus, your courage is incontestable. \n\nIf you are ready to swear your allegiance to the Covenant, we would welcome you into the Order.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.

Based on what I've heard from Adjudicator Lethold and Lumen Morellus, your courage is incontestable. \n\nIf you are ready to swear your allegiance to the Covenant, we would welcome you into the Order.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.

Now that you have joined our righteous ranks, you'll find we have ample opportunity for spreading the light. \n\nMissions are always available here and anywhere on Aeternum where our banner flies. I have Covenant gear, as well.
We'll use all the aid we can get.  Or, perhaps you would enlist in an even greater conflict?
Go with honor.
Scram! Food's for Marauders only. If you want to be fed around here, you gotta earn it.
Aye, welcome back and indeed welcome to the crew.  There'll be enough stew to feed an army, help yourself any time.
You are new here, yes? Stick around and maybe you learn how to lift.
Keep lifting, trainee. Don't let "good enough" be good enough.
Not sick, are you?  I don't have the time to treat outsiders unless you need something amputated. Always have time for that.
As a fellow Marauder, I am required to tell you that I may render first aid upon request. I am not required to tell you how much it will hurt. \n\nDon't forget you come back when you die…
Never want to be stuck in a box again. Never thought it could happen to me. One bonk to the head, and BAM!  Thanks again for the spring!
They still let me join, even after getting stuck. Perks of being friends with the rep, I suppose.  I better pay attention and practice.
Once I finish my training, we are going to absolutely SMASH!
If you would like to join our crew, you will first need to make your plea to Strou'dahia.  You will be challenged, so be prepared.

From the first, we knew you were one of us. It's in the way you carry yourself, you see? \n\nStrou'dahia has vouched for your valor, so it's time. Pledge our oaths and join our ranks, the choice is yours.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.

From the first, we knew you were one of us. It's in the way you carry yourself, you see? \n\nStrou'dahia has vouched for your valor, so it's time. Pledge our oaths and join our ranks, the choice is yours.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.
Hail, warrior! You are a credit to our ranks. \n\nDo you seek more glory? Look no further. Missions are available here and anywhere else our banner flies. I also have arms and armor, if you need.
Aye, looking strong. Which noble cause draws you?  Or, perhaps you seek assignment to even greater conflict?
Tread softly.
Ah, you have that look about you. Does she speak to you as well?   I hear the whispers of Aeternum. Not all are as blessed as we.
You're back. She said you'd be back.

When you've been around as long as I have, you start to wonder about the places you aren't supposed to be, the things you aren't supposed to see. \n\nWhat better place for that special wonder than the Syndicate!
People call me a scoundrel, but I haven't been this happy in ages.  Do you know anyone that needs their pockets picked? A temple scouted? A house robbed? Give me a holler!
A newcomer! Care for a drink?  I don't get many volunteers these days…
You're looking thirsty. Could I interest you in the latest homebrew?  I'm getting few reports of ill effects this time!
How did she get that nickname, they think.  Then, BANG! It hits them.
Aye, I am glad you joined us.  Never forget the way you reacted when I fired that one round!
Should you wish to stalk about here freely, you must get approved by Cabalist Elsayad first.   This is a sanctum, after all.
Aventus came over here six times, to tell me about you and the wolves. Six. Times. \n\nI only needed the letter from Cleo. Should you wish to join us, it is but a pen stroke away.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.
Aventus came over here six times, to tell me about you and the wolves. Six. Times. \n\nI only needed the letter from Cleo. Should you wish to join us, it is but a pen stroke away.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for another {factionCooldownDays} days.
I'd ask you to reconsider your faction alignment, but according the the Pact we cannot recruit you for one more day.

Well, then, another fox finds the den. I expect to see your name on many papers these days. \n\nCare to bolster that reputation of yours some more? I also have equipment available, should you find the need.
Everything is in motion now.  I need a fixer, and that means you.  Or, perhaps you seek assignment to even greater conflict?
Wandering without knowledge of your destination? How curious.
The quest for knowledge and understanding is our sworn duty.  Return when you understand more.\n[ Level 24 required for "Trial of the Scrivener"]
The quest for knowledge and understanding is our sworn duty. How may I service you, fellow erudite?
Oh this will be fascinating! A Marauder brute here in the Enclave. I look forward to learning from your blunders.
Yes, come hither my senseless friend. Tell me again how belief in fairy tales helps to solve all of mankind's ills. I never tire of it.

Ah, a fellow ponderer of perpetual mysteries. And an accomplished one at that!

Yes, I know about you, {playerName}. You are here to face the trial for the rank of Scrivener?
[ Level 24 required for "Trial of the Scrivener"]
Ah, a fellow ponderer of perpetual mysteries. And an accomplished one at that!\n\nYes, I know about you, {playerName}. You are here to face the trial for the rank of Scrivener?

Mark my words, {playerName}! You will be famous for assisting in my experiment!

Imagine what we can accomplish by harvesting soul traces!
[ Level 24 required for "Trial of the Chronicler"]
Mark my words, {playerName}! You will be famous for assisting in my experiment!\n\nImagine what we can accomplish by harvesting soul traces!

I see you have returned, my brightest pupil! Yes, we have much to do.

It is time to find the true essence of the Lost! 
[ Level 24 required for "Trial of the Chronicler"]
I see you have returned, my brightest pupil! Yes, we have much to do. It is time to find the true essence of the Lost!

You are back? Good, yes! I still have many thoughts on the Lost. There is so much we do not understand.

 Yet I feel closer than ever to a breakthrough!
[ Level 24 required for "Trial of the Chronicler"]
You are back? Good, yes! I still have many thoughts on the Lost. There is so much we do not understand. Yet I feel closer than ever to a breakthrough!

More traces. Yes, that is what I need. If I could only get more of them to bind them in a catalyst that would be…

 Ah, hello! I did not see you there, my friend! 
[ Level 43 required for "Trial of the Cabalist"]
More traces. Yes, that is what I need. If I could only get more of them to bind in a catalyst that would be… Ah, hello! I did not see you there, my friend!

They've told me I've reached too far for too long. I will show them what the Lost have to offer.

I mean, er-- theoretically of course. Yes, nothing to worry about my friend!
[ Level 56 required for "Trial of the Alchemist"]
They've told me I've reached too far for too long. I will show them what the Lost have to offer. I mean, er-- theoretically of course. Yes, nothing to worry about my friend!

You are an invaluable asset to our cause. I will not let the work you've done with Krockes go unnoticed. Yet I fear he has gone too far. 

Some lessons can become cautionary tales, it seems...
[ Level 56 required for "Trial of the Alchemist"]
You are an invaluable asset to our cause. I will not let the work you've done with Krockes go unnoticed. Yet I fear he has gone too far. \n\nSome lessons can become cautionary tales, it seems…

While the truth might not always be easy to find, the line between madness and brilliance can at times be even more difficult to discern.

I know you have learned this lesson well.
[ Level 56 required for "Trial of the Alchemist"]
While the truth might not always be easy to find, the line between madness and brilliance can at times be even more difficult to discern.\n\nI know you have learned this lesson well.

While the tragedy of First Light's fall is not lost on me, there remains much to discover within these new lands.

Ancient secrets of such potency haven't been seen since Brimstone.
[ Expansion required for "Trial of the Magus"]
While the tragedy of First Light's fall is not lost on me, there remains much to discover within these new lands.\n\nAncient secrets of such potency haven't been seen since Brimstone.

Ah, our newest Magus. It makes me proud to see you achieve your potential, after having done so much work for our cause.

I am quite certain these ancient relics will prove invaluable to the Syndicate.
[ Level 63 required for "Trial of the Magus"]

Ah, our newest Magus. It makes me proud to see you achieve your potential, after having done so much work for our cause.\n\nI am quite certain these ancient relics will prove invaluable to the Syndicate.
Winifred Silas, Commander of the Marauders.\n\nIn this harsh place, only the strongest will survive.

Every second is a struggle here.

There are frequent attacks from the Corrupted and an endless supply of pirates seeking to pilfer our supplies.
[ Level 20 required for the "Trial of the Gladiator" Quest ]
Every second is a struggle here.\n\nThere are frequent attacks from the Corrupted and an endless supply of pirates seeking to pilfer our supplies.
You only have the luxury to keep your nose stuck in your books because we Marauders have the courage to spill blood.
You cultists always seem to scarper when the Corrupted are at our gates.

More meat for the grinder. You've built quite a reputation around here. We'll see if it's well-deserved. 

So you think you're ready to advance? Not sure I should even allow you the chance.
[ Level 20 required for the "Trial of the Gladiator" Quest ]
More meat for the grinder. You've built quite a reputation around here. We'll see if it's well-deserved. \n\nSo you think you're ready to advance? Not sure I should even allow you the chance.

You think just because you've crushed one Lost captain and his lackeys you're ready to lead Marauders?

Feh! You've earned a new rank, but it'll end here. You'll see.
[ Level 24 required for the "Trial of the Gladiator" Quest ]
You think just because you've crushed one Lost captain and his lackeys you're ready to lead Marauders?\n\nFeh! You've earned a new rank, but it'll end here. You'll see.

Back in one piece? Pity. I was sure you'd be Lost by now. No matter, this next task will choke the life from you. This trial should prove far tougher.

I doubt you're up for the challenge.
[ Level 24 required for the "Trial of the Ravager" Quest ]
Back in one piece? Pity. I was sure you'd be Lost by now. No matter, this next task will choke the life from you. This trial should prove far tougher.\n\nI doubt you're up for the challenge.
Another fluke! It has to be. Your luck will run out eventually. And when it does, your death will be on your own conscience!\n\nNow get out of my sight, go bother somebody who cares.
What are you expecting, a salute? You think because I've been reprimanded by Gladiator Strou'dahia that I'll buckle that easy?\n\nYou'll find out how a real Marauder fights soon enough.
Fancy seeing you again! Saw you talking with Silas and thought I caught wind that you're looking for your next rank.\n\nI can give you a pointer if you tell me where she's sending you.

I see you managed to pull it off, well done. I would still remain vigilant against Silas.\n\nNow that I think on it, I think Silas had lost a bet a long while back against Lawrence and his gang. Maybe that's why she sent you.
You're on your next trial I see. I expect it wasn't a problem for you, you don't look worse for wear. Well not any worse than usual. What've you had to do?

You did more than was expected, though it's unfortunate that your trials have been turned upside down by Silas's sloppy work.\n\nSending you to take on those beasts was a lot to ask. She seems to have it out for you, but why?

A ways back, there was a Marauder by the name of Florent. He was all that the Marauders should be. He was the best of us.

But unfortunately even the best of us are still susceptible to Corruption.
[ Level 56 required for the "Trial of the Commander" Quest ]
A ways back, there was a Marauder by the name of Florent. He was all that the Marauders should be. He was the best of us.\n\nBut unfortunately even the best of us are still susceptible to Corruption.
You did what was right, and that is all I can ask of you. Thank you, friend.\n\nWhat you did means more than you could know. And as for Silas well-- she'll get what's coming to her.
I still can't believe she stole it, my only memory of Florent.\n\nHe was the best of us and it was a way for me to remember the old days we spent together.

You did good. It was a tough job dealing with Silas. It was a difficult ask but you handled it well. You deserve the title of Commander.\n\n And thanks for getting that amulet back. It means a lot to me.
You've done a great deal for the Marauders. Did I hear right that you started the Trial of the Champion?\n\nYou know that's a rare opportunity, not many get the chance to even participate.
Proud to call you a Champion of the Marauders. Brings a tear to my eye knowing I had you gathering ears way back. But see now, it all worked out didn't it?\n\nI like to think I taught you humilty.
Though your journey has been difficult, you have handled it well. I am proud to see you ascend through the ranks.
Always a welcome to sight to see one of our strongest soldiers return from battle. I trust you've recovered Florent's amulet?

Silas was a leader of the Marauders. But she has failed. She has failed not only us, but herself.

 And now she has given into the Corruption. A path no one can return from.
[ Level 56 required for the "Trial of the Commander" Quest ]
Silas was a leader of the Marauders. But she has failed. She has failed not only us, but herself.\n\n And now she has given into the Corruption. A path no one can return from.

You did well, dealing with Silas. She was a Marauder, but a lesson as well to us all, what might happen when we tread too close to the power that lies in anger.

And what happens when you refuse to let go of your grudges.
[ Level 63 required for the "Trial of the Champion" Quest ]

You did well, dealing with Silas. She was a Marauder, but a lesson as well to us all, what might happen when we tread too close to the power that lies in anger.\n\nAnd what happens when you refuse to let go of your grudges.

I have seen you rise through the ranks as a Marauder. It is no easy feat, but I know you are not one to rest on your laurels, yes?

Because a Marauder is always hungry to prove themselves.
[  Expansion required for "Trial of the Champion" Quest  ]
I have seen you rise through the ranks as a Marauder. It is no easy feat, but I know you are not one to rest on your laurels, yes?\n\nBecause a Marauder is always hungry to prove themselves.

You are truly a Champion of the Marauders. What you have done will be remembered since time immemorial.\n\nCelebrate your victories, Champion. But remember, no great leader will rest on their laurels.

You are truly a Champion of the Marauders. What you have done will be remembered since time immemorial.\n\nCelebrate your victories, Champion. But remember, no great leader will rest on their laurels.
My child, not chosing a path is still a choice. It's never too late to leave darkness for the ligt.
You carry the light with you, my friend. It will be my sacred honor to assist you.
You carry the light with you, my friend. It will be my sacred honor to assist you.
Well you certainly look strong! But in our Enclave, we prefer strength of character. Choices do have consequences, and I'm afraid you've chosen unwisely, Marauder.
So much rushing about, trying to learn everything. Some things must be taken on faith, friend. All you need is belief in the Spark.

Initiates are always eager to prove their worth. Though I must say you seem unusually well prepared.

The task at hand may demand much of you. Are you prepared to face your trial and become a Templar?
[ Level 20 required for "Trial of the Templar" Quest ]

Initiates are always eager to prove their worth. Though I must say you seem unusually well prepared.\n\nThe task at hand may demand much of you. Are you prepared to face your trial and become a Templar?
Luca has given in to the corruption. She has lost her senses!
You've seen how she turned on us. She's fallen to the Corruption.

Speak with Lethold. I have much to consider. Though, I would be remiss if I did not thank you for your help.

I don't know what would've happened if you had not been there.
[  Level 56 required for "Trial of the Adjudicator" Quest  ]
Speak with Lethold. I have much to consider. Though, I would be remiss if I did not thank you for your help. I don't know what would've happened if you had not been there.

I did what I must, but… I regret how things turned out for Luca's family. No parent should outlive their child.

Regardless, you did your part and acted with honor.
[  Level 63 required for "Trial of the Paladin" Quest  ]
